<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101433270737130></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101433270737130><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=2336&mid=101433270737130>Solo at 22</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=2336&mid=101433270737130#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=81857><span id= >voadkyn</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>16 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Feb 21st 6:05 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok peoples...this is an EASY quest for the exceptional stats.<br><br>Just hit 22 (druid) and I figured I give this a shot.&nbsp;&nbsp;Ran to Qeynos, dropped the Erudite 2gp for the book container and then spent 24gp for the jester card (got it on my sixth try).<br><br>So then I cruised over to HPH and checked out the camp.  Since I was a bit nervous with everyone talking about the smuggler that cons RED, I kept camoflaged while I camped...also since I wasn't sure, when I logged out (went to dinner 30 minutes after checking camp), I logged out next to the building, by the docks.<br><br>Well...after dinner, I relogged and set up behind the first tree on your left when you enter the smuggler's camp ground clearing.  You should be looking across the camp, at a kiln and an oven.  Inbetween these two, there is a lamp post...that is where Dyllin will spawn.  I got lucky.  After I relogged, he spawned within the hour.<br><br>Now...pathing on the RED smuggler.  His resting spot, if you are facing the lamp post, is to the right.  He will walk down to the water tunnel and sit there for a few, walk back to the campsite, up the ramp to your left, and then return to his resting spot.  Once Dyllin spawns, wait for the RED smuggler to enter the cave that leads to the water tunnel...once he does, LAY WASTE ON DYLLIN.  Run up to Dyllin, and attack.  I started off snaring him, but as long as you are in his face, he sticks to you.  He does try to run at the end, but as long as you have enough for one more spell, you should easily get him.  I nailed him with careless lightning, and at level 22, ended up with half health and half mana.<br><br>This quest is highly doable solo...and +10 wis/mana is a great reward.<br><br>Hope this helps.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
